programme.title: La Famille Blaireau-Renard
programme.desc: Les enfants découvrent un tunnel sombre et mystérieux. Aussitôt Roussette et Carcajou veulent aller l'explorer, mais Glouton fait tout pour retarder l'exploration, n'osant pas avouer qu'il a peur du noir.

programme.title: La cabane à histoires

programme.title: Sam et Julia
programme.desc: Julia a emménagé dans la même résidence que Sam. Les aventures rigolotes des deux souriceaux vont permettre à Julia de mieux s'intégrer dans cet environnement différent qui, jour après jour, devient un peu plus le sien.

programme.title: Droners
programme.desc: Corto impressionne tout le monde par une incroyable victoire sur le fil grâce à son talent de pilote. Mais la prochaine course repose sur les connaissances des ingenerds. Enki aimerait bien mener son équipe vers la victoire.

programme.title: Api !
programme.desc: Mouss est surpris : il entend Api prendre sa défense. Pourtant, n'est-elle pas son ennemie jurée ?

programme.title: Comme des têtes pas de poule

programme.desc: Una guardia en Bahía Guantánamo inicia una extraña amistad con uno de los detenidos más antiguos en la instalación.

programme.title: La noche del demonio: La última llave
programme.desc: Una prestigiosa parapsicóloga y su equipo se desplazan a Nuevo México para investigar los fenómenos que ocurren en la casa en la que ella creció. Allá, ella deberá enfrentarse a su mayor miedo: el demonio que sin querer liberó en el pasado.

programme.title: Línea mortal: Al límite
programme.desc: Cinco estudiantes de medicina experimentan a propósito experiencias cercanas a la muerte. Mientras más se aproximan al umbral del otro mundo, las consecuencias paranormales de su investigación repercuten con más intensidad en sus vidas.

programme.title: Noche de venganza
programme.desc: Un policía con conexiones en el submundo criminal registra un club nocturno en búsqueda de su hijo secuestrado.

programme.title: S.W.A.T.: Bajo asedio
programme.desc: Un cuartel de policía es sitiado después de que un agente doble del cartel sea arrestado por el S.W.A.T. de Seattle.

programme.title: Django sin cadenas
programme.desc: Un exesclavo une fuerzas con un cazador de recompensas alemán que lo liberó y lo ayuda a buscar a los criminales más buscados del sur de los Estados Unidos, con la esperanza de reencontrarse con su esposa.

programme.title: Nuestra última aventura
programme.desc: John y Ella Spencer, dos ancianos cansados de los consejos y advertencias de hijos y médicos, hacen un viaje por carretera, probablemente el último de sus vidas, en su casa rodante. La pareja sale de Boston y se dirige a Florida.

programme.title: El gran casamiento

programme.title: Buscando
programme.desc: Después de que su hija de 16 años desaparece, un padre desesperado accede a la computadora portátil de la adolescente en busca de pistas para encontrarla.

programme.title: La torre oscura

programme.title: Karate Kid

programme.title: La cruda verdad

programme.title: Nube siniestra
programme.desc: Usando un entorno de realidad virtual para identificar la ubicación de bombas, dos genios invaden la memoria de terroristas.

programme.title: El tipo perfecto

programme.title: Amityville: El despertar
programme.desc: Una ambiciosa periodista decide hacer un reportaje para revelar los escalofriantes sucesos ocurridos en Amityville en 1976. Ahora, los siniestros hechos de la casa atormentarán a una familia recién mudada.

programme.title: Cambios inesperados

programme.desc: Un romántico empedernido cree que encontró el amor verdadero. Sin embargo, pronto descubre que su pareja lo está utilizando para vengarse de su marido.

programme.desc: Un agente caído en desgracia respalda a un operador de códigos de la CIA en una estación en el desierto de Nevada después de que este sufre un ataque inesperado.

programme.title: Los huérfanos
programme.desc: Un espíritu maligno atormenta a cuatro hermanos después de la muerte de la matriarca de la familia. Los fenómenos paranormales dejan paso, poco a poco, a manifestaciones sobrenaturales cada vez más espeluznantes.

programme.title: El despertar del zodiaco
programme.desc: Una desafortunada pareja descubre los carretes de una película de un asesino serial.

programme.title: Seduciendo a un extraño
programme.desc: Una reportera se cruza en el camino de un poderoso ejecutivo cuando empieza a trabajar de forma encubierta para investigar la muerte sin resolver de un amigo.

programme.title: Rendirse Jamás 3
programme.desc: Case Walker, un ex campeón de la MMA, empieza su regreso en el deporte en busca de otro título, y utiliza sus habilidades de la escuela secundaria en contra de los nuevos peleadores.

programme.title: Nueve perfectos extraños
programme.desc: Llega el momento de que todos crucen el umbral y se enfrenten a sus demonios, incluida Masha. Es posible que se revelen las respuestas largamente esperadas.

programme.title: The Lady Refuses
programme.desc: A rich man (Gilbert Emery) hires a woman (Betty Compson) to rescue his son (John Darrow) from a gold digger.

programme.title: Tulsa
programme.desc: A cattle rancher's daughter (Susan Hayward) turns Oklahoma wildcatter with a geologist (Robert Preston) and an Indian (Pedro Armendáriz) as partners.

programme.title: The Intruder
programme.desc: A charismatic stranger (William Shatner) stirs up racist sentiments in a small town to prevent school integration from happening there.

programme.title: House of the Stone Monkeys
programme.desc: The lives of two boys who lived in the same Budapest apartment, 30 years apart.

programme.title: Mr. Wong, Detective
programme.desc: A chemical manufacturer receives death threats after he obtains the rights to an odorless and lethal gas.

programme.title: Port of New York
programme.desc: Customs agents (Scott Brady, Richard Rober) pound the pavement for clues to nab the head (Yul Brynner) of a yacht-club narcotics ring.

programme.title: Too Late for Tears
programme.desc: A woman (Lizabeth Scott) kills her husband and plots with a private eye (Dan Duryea) after someone tosses a moneybag into her car.

programme.title: Paradise Canyon
programme.desc: A federal agent tracks down a gang of counterfeiters operating along the Mexican border.

programme.title: Smash-Up: The Story of a Woman
programme.desc: A nightclub singer (Susan Hayward) turns alcoholic after quitting her career to marry a rising singer (Lee Bowman).

programme.title: Footprints on the Moon
programme.desc: A woman becomes possessed by the mental screams of an astronaut who was stranded on the surface of the moon.

programme.title: When a Dream Comes True
programme.desc: Ed risks everything, including his family and business venture, to try to make his childhood dream of becoming a filmmaker in the United States come true.

programme.title: One More Time
programme.desc: An 80-year-old actress returns to the Chilean town of her youth to create a television show in a place without TVs.

programme.title: Jack London
programme.desc: The writer (Michael O'Shea) joins the Alaskan gold rush, goes to sea, finds a wife (Susan Hayward) and covers the Russo-Japanese War.

programme.title: A Dog's Life
programme.desc: Charlie rescues a stray from other dogs, and together they meet Edna after finding a wallet full of cash.

programme.title: Behind Green Lights
programme.desc: A cub reporter (Richard Crane) hangs around the police station, and an officer (William Gargan) falls for a murder suspect (Carole Landis).

programme.title: A Christmas Wish
programme.desc: Rupert, a dancing squirrel, is left to fend for himself on the streets after his master turns bankrupt; unsuited for the hard life, Rupert devises a scheme to raise his master's family from poverty.

programme.title: The Ghost of Sierra de Cobre
programme.desc: Vivia Mandore, an heiress, enlists the services of a paranormal investigator to look into a suspected case of haunting involving the spirit of her deceased mother-in-law.

programme.title: Parole, Inc.
programme.desc: A G-man (Michael O'Shea) poses as a convict to trap a parole fixer (Turhan Bey) in the state prison.

programme.title: Gesture
programme.desc: Ali learns about the sudden recurrence of his son's incurable genetic disorder. Deciding to hide the matter from the rest of the family, he finds himself helpless and behaving erratically.

programme.title: The Tall T
programme.desc: An outlaw (Richard Boone) and his men hold an heiress (Maureen O'Sullivan), her cowardly husband and a rancher (Randolph Scott).

programme.title: Champagne Safari
programme.desc: The marriage of Hollywood goddess Rita Hayworth and Prince Aly Khan is celebrated.

programme.title: The Ape
programme.desc: A mad doctor (Boris Karloff) poses as an ape and kills people for bodily fluids to help a disabled girl.

programme.title: Voyage to the Planet of Prehistoric Women
programme.desc: Astronauts are surprised when they encounter dangerous monsters and beautiful women after their spaceship crashes on Venus.

programme.title: Trapped
programme.desc: An ex-counterfeiter (Lloyd Bridges) leads an undercover agent (John Hoyt) to a gang using his best plates.

programme.title: Anna Christie
programme.desc: Based on the play by Eugene O'Neill. A young woman's shady past threatens her relationship with the sailor she loves.

programme.title: The Phantom Father
programme.desc: Robert (Marcel Iures) journeys through Bucovina to find Sami (Valer Delakeza), the only person that can tell him about his Romanian Jewish ancestry.

programme.title: Captain Calamity
programme.desc: Pirates change course for a South Seas captain (George Houston) who says he found a sunken Spanish treasure.

programme.title: The North Star
programme.desc: Members (Anne Baxter, Dana Andrews, Walter Huston) of a Ukrainian farm collective become guerrillas to fight the Nazis.

programme.title: The Great Flamarion
programme.desc: A vaudeville marksman (Erich von Stroheim) accidentally shoots his assistant's (Mary Beth Hughes) husband (Dan Duryea).

programme.title: Operation Bottleneck
programme.desc: World War II paratroopers stage a rescue mission in Burma to recover a wounded officer taken prisoner by the Japanese.

programme.title: Brides
programme.desc: A seamstress tries to keep her life together for her two children when her lover is sent to prison for 10 years.

programme.title: The Black Book
programme.desc: An enemy (Robert Cummings) of Robespierre (Richard Basehart) steals the secret book listing his candidates for the guillotine.

programme.title: Délicate gravité
programme.desc: A man receives a message on his phone from an unknown woman who sounds suicidal.

programme.title: Velo Mysterium
programme.desc: The symbiotic relationship between human and bicycle.

programme.title: Bulldog Drummond's Peril
programme.desc: The British sleuth (John Howard) marries Phyllis (Louise Campbell) and nabs diamond counterfeiters for a Scotland Yard colonel (John Barrymore).

programme.title: Love Laughs at Andy Hardy
programme.desc: The judge's (Lewis Stone) son (Mickey Rooney) goes to college after serving in the war and finds his sweetheart (Bonita Granville) is engaged to someone else.

programme.title: Our Quarantine
programme.desc: In Rome, a university teacher has forced a young student to follow the story of 16 Moroccan workers for reasons of study and for reasons of life. Salvatore, one of the students, could possibly learn something from the assignment.

programme.title: Flesh and Fury
programme.desc: A gold digger (Jan Sterling) and a newswoman (Mona Freeman) follow a deaf boxer's (Tony Curtis) fight to regain his hearing and win the title.

programme.title: Stuck
programme.desc: A couple develops marital problems.

programme.title: Lady of Burlesque
programme.desc: Burlesque dancer Dixie Daisy is the prime suspect when rival dancers are found strangled with their own stage costumes. Aided by infatuated stand-up comic Biff Brannigan, Dixie must find the killer before she becomes his next victim.

programme.title: Broadway Limited
programme.desc: An actress (Marjorie Woodworth), producer and secretary are taken for kidnappers when their PR stunt backfires on a train.

programme.title: The Hoodlum
programme.desc: A paroled career criminal (Lawrence Tierney) betrays his family's trust by masterminding an armored car robbery.

programme.title: Sunny
programme.desc: The heir (Anna Neagle) to an auto fortune falls in love with a circus star (Ray Bolger) in New Orleans during Mardi Gras.

programme.title: Sherlock - Terror By Night

programme.title: The Southerner
programme.desc: Poor white tenant farmers (Zachary Scott, Betty Field, Beulah Bondi) battle fierce odds to make a living on a Texas plot.

programme.title: Silver on the Sage
programme.desc: Hopalong Cassidy (William Boyd) pins rustling on a casino owner and his twin brother (Stanley Ridges).

programme.title: Suddenly
programme.desc: A hit man (Frank Sinatra) and company plan to shoot the president when he gets off his train in Suddenly, Calif.

programme.title: Mutiny
programme.desc: Americans (Mark Stevens, Patric Knowles) try to smuggle gold from France to use against the British in the War of 1812.

programme.title: Frieda

programme.title: Fear and Desire
programme.desc: Four soldiers must confront their fears and desires behind enemy lines.

programme.title: Death and the Knight
programme.desc: Secluded for ages within his tower, a knight is awoken from his slumber by a mysterious whisper and sets off on a perilous journey to find an elusive enemy.

programme.title: Too Late for Tears
programme.desc: A woman (Lizabeth Scott) kills her husband and plots with a private eye (Dan Duryea) after someone tosses a moneybag into her car.

programme.title: Edith

programme.title: Go for Broke!
programme.desc: An Army lieutenant (Van Johnson) leads the Japanese-American 442nd Regimental Combat Team to World War II glory.

programme.title: Badge of Honor
programme.desc: An out-of-town socialite (Buster Crabbe) plays newsman and becomes a hero.

programme.title: Padre
programme.desc: Mourning the death of her father, Giulia is contacted by him from the other dimension.

programme.title: Mother

programme.title: The Amazing Adventure
